The paper discusses a new isolation abstraction for serverless big data computing, which involves memory sharing between functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of software-fault isolation (SFI) and WebAssembly, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the runtime for Faaslets, which involves resource isolation and a low-level POSIX host interface, suggesting that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions machine learning models and inference, which could be related to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
